WorldStage NewsOnlineâ€”-Femi Gbajabiamila, member of the House of Representatives (APC-Lagos) has officially joined the race for the office of the Speaker of the 9th Assembly. Gbajabiamila, in company of 170 members-elect, made his intention known on Sunday in Abuja. Gbajabiamila said he was in the race to unite the nation and to bring good governance closer to the people. If elected speaker, Gbajabiamila said that he would galvanise the lawmakers to make life more abundant for all Nigerians. He said there was much work to be done by way of legislation in the area of education, health, power, infrastructure and alleviation of poverty.